Pipe Break at Shota Rustaveli: Transportation Movement Changed

05 Nov 2019, 15:08

In Kiev, a number of public transport routes have changed traffic because of a pipe break at Shota Rustaveli.
Due to the breakthrough of the heating network on Shota Rustaveli Street in Kyiv, public transport was to be changed.
Changes in the routes of trolleybuses and buses due to the accident are reported by Kyivpastrans.

Currently, the traffic is organized as follows:


trolleybuses №40 and №40K ply to the railway massif;
trolleybuses №3 and №9 - to the southern railway station;
trolleybuses №12 - to the station. Lybidska;
trolleybuses №14 - to the station. m. Sports Palace;
buses №69 - to the street. Tarasivska.

Read: In Kiev, because of the accident, Saksagansky Street flooded with boiling water
It was reported that a hot water pipe burst at the intersection of Shota Rustaveli and Saksagansky streets in Kiev. Several cars crashed into the pits that were the result of the accident.
